<p>A great example of a tight one-sheeter that covers every essential element and uses the space and graphics perfectly:</p>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/one20sheeter20examples20startup20incubtor.png" alt="one sheeter examples startup incubator" width="800" height="1133" class="aligncenter" /></div>
<h3>Mercedes-Benz one-sheeter</h3>
<p>A well-known brand that uses <a href="/blog/ws/2014/12/17/science-of-emotion-in-marketing-courtney-seiter">emotions</a> and visualization. Itâ€™s all benefits, nothing about features or pain points. But hey, itâ€™s Mercedes-Benz. They donâ€™t have to do much selling.</p>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/one-sheeter20examples20mercedes20benz.png" alt="one-sheeter examples mercedes benz" width="800" height="1148" class="aligncenter" /></div>
<h3>Tech agency one-sheeter</h3>
<p>Fantastic one-sheeter that utilizes space and graphics to capture everything they do in a single sheet. The <a href="/blog/ws/2017/05/17/how-to-write-great-headlines">headline is intriguing</a> and grabs your attention.</p>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/one20sheeter20tech20agency20example.png" alt="tech agency one sheeter example" width="800" height="1035" class="aligncenter" /></div>
