<p><strong>Step 3</strong></p>
<p>Lastly, you&#8217;re going to set the time and frequency of your automated rule:</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="b85781a1-e944-4fb2-a865-05a29dca31aa" data-langcode="und">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/google-ads-holiday-automation-pause-2-1.png" alt="Google Ads Holiday Automation Pause" width="827" height="322" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>Select â€œOnceâ€ in the frequencyÂ drop-down, and choose 12 AM for the day you want the campaign to pause. In thisÂ example, Iâ€™ve instructed Google AdsÂ to pause theÂ campaign on November 28 â€“ and <strong>it will remain paused until I enable it again</strong> (more on this later). Set theÂ â€œusing data fromâ€ fieldÂ to &#8220;Same day&#8221; (as opposed to &#8220;Same month&#8221; in the example here). Finally, you may want to assign a custom â€œRule nameâ€ to your automation because it will help you identify your rules later on when you want to review them.</p>
<p>You can also select the option to receive an email when your rule actually takes effect or leave it set to email you only when a rule changes or if thereâ€™s an error in your rule, but thatâ€™s generally only going to come into play when youâ€™re doing more sophisticated automations.</p>
<p>Hit â€œSaveâ€ and youâ€™re done!</p>
<p><strong>One last step</strong></p>
<p>Okay, not quite done. I mentioned the need to enable your soon-to-be-paused accounts after the desired paused period has elapsed. You can set this to happen automatically for you so you donâ€™t forget in your post-holiday grogginess.</p>
<p>Simply follow step one above, but this time select â€œEnable campaignsâ€¦â€</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="41785ad4-ea08-4607-b251-c03187d74bc7" data-langcode="und">
